Vergil died in 19 B.c., and the Aeneid must have been published shortly after. The principate of Augustus lasted on to Α. D. 14, thirty-two years later (735-767)‚ and the question now confronts us in a new shape.

Is ‘AETNA' AUGUSTAN?
